102
00:08:37,922 --> 00:08:38,682
My name is Adam Knight.

103
00:08:39,022 --> 00:08:40,983
I'm a candidate for reelection to the Medford city council.

104
00:08:41,743 --> 00:08:42,724
I'm number four in your ballot.

105
00:08:43,064 --> 00:08:44,624
And I'd ask for your consideration on November 7th.

106
00:08:44,744 --> 00:08:47,345
Um, a little bit about myself.

107
00:08:47,466 --> 00:08:52,167
I reside in West Medford with my wife, Alison and our sons, Ryan and Brendan, uh, Ryan's three and Brendan's one.

108
00:08:52,868 --> 00:08:55,949
I'm a product of the Medford public schools graduating from MHS in 1996.

109
00:08:56,309 --> 00:09:00,471
I then went on to earn a bachelor's degree in political science from Merrimack college.

110
00:09:00,915 --> 00:09:03,516
and a master's degree in public administration from Suffolk University.

111
00:09:04,637 --> 00:09:19,864
I have nearly 20 years' experience working in government, first for the late State Senator Charlie Shannon as his Director of Constituent Services, then as an organizer, a field representative, and a contract negotiator in the labor movement, and now as an arbitrator with the Executive Office of Labor and Workforce Development.

112
00:09:20,804 --> 00:09:28,508
It's through these experiences that I've had the opportunity to work on many initiatives that have made a difference in our community, items like marriage equality,

113
00:09:29,487 --> 00:09:36,971
affordable health care, the long-term leasing of our skating rinks, Flint and La Conte, the school building assistance program, and the Greenland extension, just to name a few.

114
00:09:38,291 --> 00:09:50,617
And I think it's safe to say that in a city that has a $166 million operating budget and a council that's made $13 million worth of appropriations in the past two years, that qualifications and experience do matter.

115
00:09:51,621 --> 00:09:56,127
I'm very grateful to have earned your trust and to have had the opportunity to serve as your city councilor for the past four years.

116
00:09:56,607 --> 00:10:00,853
And since my election, I've always embraced the philosophy that results are more important than rhetoric.

117
00:10:01,310 --> 00:10:04,271
and this has been a very successful council that's produced a number of results.

118
00:10:05,051 --> 00:10:13,233
From a legislative standpoint, I've worked with my colleagues to implement changes to our city ordinances that benefits our quality of life and improves the operation of government.

119
00:10:14,393 --> 00:10:23,836
Successfully fighting for measures that have reformed the vehicle for higher ordinance to better protect consumers, increased the legal age to purchase tobacco products in the community to protect our public health,

120
00:10:24,895 --> 00:10:33,038
the implementation of a university accountability ordinance to safeguard our neighborhoods, and the wage theft ordinance to ensure proper distribution of tax dollars to public contractors.

121
00:10:34,458 --> 00:10:36,679
From a financial standpoint, the city's on solid ground.

122
00:10:37,339 --> 00:10:40,500
For the first time in recent memory, the city's passed a unanimous budget.

123
00:10:41,721 --> 00:10:49,864
We have suitable reserves and an A++ bond rating, allowing us to borrow at low rates, and a capital plan allowing us flexibility to meet our demands and spending needs.

124
00:10:51,484 --> 00:10:53,645
Today, our streets are safer.

125
00:10:54,865 --> 00:10:57,467
We've reduced the speed limit on city streets to 25 miles an hour.

126
00:10:58,128 --> 00:11:00,750
We've created and funded positions in the budget to combat addiction.

127
00:11:01,510 --> 00:11:05,333
We've purchased 12 new police cars and critical equipment for our fire department.

128
00:11:05,934 --> 00:11:13,000
But most importantly, we've appropriated $2 million for the design of a new police station and have a commitment to deliver new police and fire headquarter buildings by the year 2020.

129
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:15,522
This is a commitment that I will not forget.

130
00:11:17,323 --> 00:11:18,104
We have great schools.

131
00:11:18,744 --> 00:11:21,927
Great schools open a world of opportunity for both our kids and our community.

132
00:11:22,375 --> 00:11:25,077
and I'm committed as a parent and as a city councilor to that end.

133
00:11:26,298 --> 00:11:36,124
In the past term, we've opened a new media center and a full service culinary arts program at MHS, expanded course offerings, implemented before school programs, and have the lowest class sizes in the region.

134
00:11:36,824 --> 00:11:43,689
In the next term, I'll work with the school committee to further expand and strengthen our opportunities for our youngsters and to deliver a new public library to the city of Medford.

135
00:11:45,230 --> 00:11:47,331
The strong infrastructure is the backbone of our community.

136
00:11:47,931 --> 00:11:52,094
We need responsive public works to provide the basic but essential services that we rely on every day.

137
00:11:53,188 --> 00:12:03,411
I've made a commitment to that end, improving service delivery with the funding of 12 new pieces of equipment for our DPW, securing over $2 million for water mains to bolster our light abatement programs.

138
00:12:04,431 --> 00:12:13,013
In the next term, I'll push to build upon this progress by fighting for increased staffing levels, improving maintenance and upkeep of our sidewalks and roadways, and improvements to our transportation infrastructure.

139
00:12:15,014 --> 00:12:19,855
Vibrant downtowns add to our economic stability and greatly contribute to the overall success of our community.

140
00:12:20,894 --> 00:12:39,529
We're making great progress addressing this priority through initiatives that help make our business district thrive, like the public-private partnership to bring headline acts to Chevalier Auditorium, the construction of the Crystal Campbell Peace Garden, the Riverside Plaza, and the Clippership Connector to generate foot traffic in our square, and most importantly, the master plan for the revitalization of Medford Square.

141
00:12:40,089 --> 00:12:43,892
Next term, I'll work with the stakeholders in our business district to ensure that we put that plan to use.

142
00:12:45,253 --> 00:12:47,555
I'm proud of the accomplishments that we've made just by working together.

143
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:54,244
We've made safe streets, great schools, strong infrastructure, and vibrant downtowns our top priorities because these are the key to a strong quality of life.

144
00:12:54,844 --> 00:12:57,426
But there is more work to be done, and I would like to be a part of this work.

145
00:12:58,567 --> 00:13:06,732
I believe I have the qualifications, the experience, and the knowledge of the issues to continue to make a positive impact on our community, and I'm asking you for the opportunity to continue to serve.

146
00:13:07,172 --> 00:13:07,872
My name's Adam Knight.

147
00:13:08,073 --> 00:13:10,334
I'm number four on the ballot, and I thank you very much for listening.

148
00:13:10,574 --> 00:13:12,335
I'd appreciate your support on November 7th.

149
00:13:12,515 --> 00:13:13,076
Thank you very much.

150
00:13:15,157 --> 00:13:16,238
Thank you, Council Knight.

151
00:13:22,126 --> 00:13:22,926
Natalie Breen.

152
00:13:28,149 --> 00:13:28,790
Hi, everyone.

153
00:13:30,811 --> 00:13:31,151
Hello.

154
00:13:32,672 --> 00:13:35,874
My name's Natalie Breen, and I am running for Medford City Council.

155
00:13:36,154 --> 00:13:45,560
I'm 24 years old, a lifelong Medford resident, and a very proud graduate of Medford Public Schools, having attended the Forest Park, the Andrews, the McGlynn, and Medford High class of 2010.

156
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:54,707
I graduated from Suffolk University in 2013 with a degree in marketing, and I now work in commercial real estate and development.

157
00:13:55,768 --> 00:14:02,274
I am also an appointed member of Medford's Commission for Persons with Disabilities, making sure the city is accessible for all.

158
00:14:03,995 --> 00:14:06,678
And I am also a first-time candidate for public office.

159
00:14:07,476 --> 00:14:16,183
My brother, Patrick, is a bagger at Stop and Shop and a graduate of Medford Public Schools as well, as well as volunteering at the Lawrence Memorial Hospital.

160
00:14:16,543 --> 00:14:21,027
My mom, Karen Breen, has been a nurse for the Medford public school system for 20 years.

161
00:14:21,927 --> 00:14:28,973
And my father is on the board for the Riverside Yacht Club here in Medford, as well as a former Medford youth girls softball coach.

162
00:14:29,153 --> 00:14:33,096
I can assure you I would be a much better city counselor than I was a softball player.

163
00:14:33,136 --> 00:14:34,197
I was very, very bad.

164
00:14:34,217 --> 00:14:36,679
My dad actually had to make a position for me so I could play.

165
00:14:37,619 --> 00:14:39,400
But that's a little bit about me.

166
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:41,000
So why am I running?

167
00:14:41,781 --> 00:14:42,561
It's pretty simple.

168
00:14:42,761 --> 00:14:43,581
I love Medford.

169
00:14:43,721 --> 00:14:44,542
I love this city.

170
00:14:44,562 --> 00:14:45,402
I grew up here.

171
00:14:45,422 --> 00:14:47,343
I plan to stay here for a long time.

172
00:14:47,443 --> 00:14:48,863
I would love to raise a family here.

173
00:14:48,883 --> 00:14:51,944
I'm very personally invested in bringing Medford to the next level.

174
00:14:53,685 --> 00:14:55,385
I want Medford to be the best it can be.

175
00:14:55,645 --> 00:15:03,108
I'm a firm believer that you can't be what you can't see, and I think we really need a young female voice on the council to speak for people in our city.

176
00:15:03,835 --> 00:15:06,256
I think I can bring a lot of energy and new ideas.

177
00:15:07,096 --> 00:15:11,999
And I grew up surrounded by people who have dedicated their lives to public service and helping others.

178
00:15:12,799 --> 00:15:18,721
My uncles are firefighters, my mother's a nurse, and I just feel this is my way to contribute back to the community.

179
00:15:19,602 --> 00:15:23,784
And while I have no past political experience, this is actually a good thing.

180
00:15:23,844 --> 00:15:27,865
It means I have no notion of how things have to be done or things have to be done a certain way.

181
00:15:27,885 --> 00:15:29,566
I can think outside the box.

182
00:15:29,786 --> 00:15:31,387
I offer a fresh new perspective.

183
00:15:32,418 --> 00:15:36,561
What's great about Medford is we have all the resources to bring Medford to the next level.

184
00:15:36,841 --> 00:15:37,682
Everything's here.

185
00:15:38,282 --> 00:15:40,664
We just need people to roll up their sleeves and make it happen.

186
00:15:41,725 --> 00:15:45,087
And when I say resources, what I'm referring to is the Mystic.

187
00:15:45,147 --> 00:15:46,428
It's flowing through our downtown.

188
00:15:46,468 --> 00:15:47,749
We're not making use of that.

189
00:15:48,390 --> 00:15:51,372
We have access to Boston by bus, train, car.

190
00:15:51,392 --> 00:15:53,533
We're so close to one of the most vibrant cities.

191
00:15:53,633 --> 00:15:58,657
We have one of the biggest national educational institutions in Tufts right here in Medford.

192
00:15:59,040 --> 00:16:02,442
We could use them a lot more, create a stronger partnership with them.

193
00:16:03,123 --> 00:16:03,964
We have the Fells.

194
00:16:04,024 --> 00:16:05,745
We have countless historic buildings.

195
00:16:05,845 --> 00:16:18,394
We have the Chevalier Theater, which I think is going to bring a lot of energy to the square, which desperately needs it, as well as the Brooks Estates, which is a passion project of mine and I think could be a really great revenue generator for the city.

196
00:16:19,643 --> 00:16:20,724
So everything's here.

197
00:16:20,784 --> 00:16:23,385
We just really need to put it together and make it happen.

198
00:16:24,085 --> 00:16:32,308
But areas that are at the top of my priority list, based on what I've talked to people about walking around the city, is one, our infrastructure.

199
00:16:32,388 --> 00:16:33,769
I think that's the bare basic.

200
00:16:33,849 --> 00:16:35,930
I've heard a lot about roads, about sidewalks.

201
00:16:35,950 --> 00:16:37,150
I think everybody can agree.

202
00:16:38,010 --> 00:16:44,493
So we definitely need to start there, making sure our roads are safe and accessible for pedestrians, cyclists, vehicle traffic.

203
00:16:45,672 --> 00:16:50,334
in making sure we are improving and maintaining our streets on a regular and reliable schedule.

204
00:16:50,694 --> 00:16:56,037
It means when a contractor comes in to do work for the city, we're making sure they leave the street better than when they found it.

205
00:16:57,052 --> 00:17:00,253
Next, public safety, so our police officers and our firefighters.

206
00:17:01,253 --> 00:17:05,934
They're understaffed, which will become more of a problem as Medford continues to grow.

207
00:17:05,974 --> 00:17:10,555
I'm sure everyone's aware of how much development is going on and how many people will be coming into the city.

208
00:17:11,795 --> 00:17:15,055
They lack resources, and they're working in subpar conditions.

