275
00:24:15,039 --> 00:24:15,639
Curtis Tootin.

276
00:24:27,541 --> 00:24:30,582
Hello, friends, honored guests, and all fellow Medford residents.

277
00:24:31,273 --> 00:24:34,175
My name is Curtis Tudin, and I am a candidate for Medford City Council.

278
00:24:34,956 --> 00:24:42,421
As a lifelong resident of this wonderful city, with years of experience working and volunteering in our community, I know I deserve your vote this election season.

279
00:24:43,162 --> 00:24:48,006
This is my first run for public office, but I have great confidence thanks to tremendous early support from residents.

280
00:24:48,566 --> 00:24:50,367
Together, we have what it takes to win.

281
00:24:51,208 --> 00:24:52,429
Frankly, we need a win right now.

282
00:24:52,929 --> 00:24:55,371
People in our city are tired of the current political climate.

283
00:24:56,031 --> 00:25:00,195
Thankfully, Medford's November 7th election is a great opportunity for change.

284
00:25:01,048 --> 00:25:06,712
Voters out there asking, why should I cast a vote, my most important civic responsibility, for a Curtis student?

285
00:25:07,172 --> 00:25:09,394
Let me tell you, there are many reasons, all of them good.

286
00:25:10,275 --> 00:25:14,178
First and foremost, I'm the best candidate in support of Medford's environment and public schools.

287
00:25:14,818 --> 00:25:24,525
My campaign is based on the need to take action in response to climate change, and my career working for Medford Public Schools gave me an ideal perspective of the city's most important public service and largest budget item.

288
00:25:25,326 --> 00:25:29,709
There are so many important steps our city can take to adapt and mitigate the effects of climate change,

289
00:25:30,383 --> 00:25:32,445
Unfortunately, our city council has lacked leadership.

290
00:25:33,065 --> 00:25:42,793
After years of volunteer service and as current chairperson of Medford's Energy and Environment Committee, I know how to increase renewable energy use and save residents money on their electricity bill at the same time.

291
00:25:43,613 --> 00:25:47,877
My first act as city councilor will be to help pass community energy aggregation in Medford.

292
00:25:48,557 --> 00:25:50,559
It's one of many steps towards meeting our goals.

293
00:25:51,179 --> 00:25:58,705
Others include fixing toxic gas leaks, planning for severe weather, expanding recycling services, supporting community gardens, and much more.

294
00:25:59,648 --> 00:26:07,231
If elected, I promise to responsibly lead Medford through all the work that needs to be done, prioritizing sustainability and protecting natural resources.

295
00:26:07,931 --> 00:26:10,932
Of course, the city's most important natural resource is our children.

296
00:26:11,512 --> 00:26:13,853
We protect and empower them by supporting public schools.

297
00:26:14,594 --> 00:26:18,995
Every day, thousands of students and their teachers do great things in Medford, but there is vast room for improvement.

298
00:26:19,575 --> 00:26:24,317
The same can be said for all public services and infrastructure, from potholes to police and fire departments.

299
00:26:24,737 --> 00:26:28,919
So if elected, I promise Medford will do more to meet the needs of its residents and workforce.

300
00:26:29,935 --> 00:26:33,677
A resolution to the opiate addiction epidemic is one need currently not being met.

301
00:26:34,358 --> 00:26:40,381
In 2016, there were over 64,000 drug overdose deaths in the United States, and Medford has suffered its share of tragedy.

302
00:26:40,922 --> 00:26:47,165
It has also taken some steps to relieve the issue, most recently by appointing a recovery counselor and supporting Team Medford programs.

303
00:26:47,646 --> 00:26:57,832
But we need to do more to end drug use stigmatization, implement additional prevention and intervention policy, and make sure there is funding available for innovative programs that address this public health crisis.

304
00:26:58,747 --> 00:27:03,689
Overall, my campaign's commitment to running free of financial donations ensures my priorities are earnest.

305
00:27:04,749 --> 00:27:10,311
By working together on municipal projects, we can achieve great things, but the key to success is not leaving anyone behind.

306
00:27:11,112 --> 00:27:19,055
Many will only, Medford, excuse me, will only progress if all community members are involved, which is why social justice issues are a primary part of my campaign.

307
00:27:19,755 --> 00:27:25,257
A clear next step is for Medford to become a sanctuary city and create policy that welcomes diversity and is free of fear.

308
00:27:26,258 --> 00:27:32,300
Then, through the process of charter reform, our city can promote equity and work to end injustice, whatever form it may take.

309
00:27:33,240 --> 00:27:37,181
Events like tonight get me excited for all the progress we can make together after election day.

310
00:27:37,841 --> 00:27:41,502
Thanks to the Medford Democratic City Committee and all volunteers who helped bring us together.

311
00:27:42,162 --> 00:27:43,643
And thanks to everyone watching the video.

312
00:27:43,863 --> 00:27:47,203
Your participation in person and online makes our democracy stronger.

313
00:27:47,844 --> 00:27:52,825
If elected, I promise to emphasize collaboration so all perspectives are represented in the political process.

314
00:27:53,686 --> 00:27:56,667
I'm working hard for your vote, but I'll work even harder as your city councilor.

315
00:27:57,348 --> 00:28:01,109
People will have unprecedented access to their local government with me as an elected official.

316
00:28:01,790 --> 00:28:06,712
Whatever the issue, Medford residents can count on me to care, listen, and give voice to their cause.

317
00:28:07,412 --> 00:28:19,697
For more information about my campaign, please call my phone at 781-572-7196, email me at curtis.tootin at gmail.com, visit votetootin2017.com, or find me on Facebook.

318
00:28:20,298 --> 00:28:23,459
Most important, make sure to vote on November 7th, and remember,

319
00:28:23,858 --> 00:28:29,659
A vote for Curtis Tudin is a vote for change at City Council, for a prosperous future, and local politics to be proud of.

320
00:28:30,199 --> 00:28:31,679
In conclusion, Go Medford.

321
00:28:31,879 --> 00:28:32,380
Vote Tudin.

