00:28:51,683 --> 00:28:52,103
Good evening.

326
00:28:53,485 --> 00:28:58,169
When I first ran for office back some 16 years ago, my slogan was, time for a change.

327
00:28:59,270 --> 00:29:01,932
Now I've updated my slogan to, experience counts.

328
00:29:04,574 --> 00:29:07,616
Let me begin by saying what I hope all of you already know about me.

329
00:29:08,216 --> 00:29:08,957
I love this city.

330
00:29:09,297 --> 00:29:11,579
It has been the passion for as long as I can remember.

331
00:29:12,139 --> 00:29:16,623
It is why I've devoted the better half of my adult life to public service here in Meffitt.

332
00:29:17,223 --> 00:29:20,465
We are poised on the threshold of a new and exciting era.

333
00:29:21,026 --> 00:29:22,427
A step forward, front and center,

334
00:29:22,918 --> 00:29:24,559
reaching into the 21st century.

335
00:29:25,859 --> 00:29:30,021
If you give me your support, your confidence, and your trust, we can soar.

336
00:29:30,641 --> 00:29:36,784
We can make our city the envy of its neighbors, the pride of its citizens, a legacy of generations to come.

337
00:29:37,504 --> 00:29:39,665
Let's make Meffitt the miracle city on the Mystic.

338
00:29:40,825 --> 00:29:42,006
What are your ideas, you ask?

339
00:29:42,864 --> 00:29:43,824
What have you accomplished?

340
00:29:44,404 --> 00:29:45,925
What can we expect from Michael Marks?

341
00:29:46,665 --> 00:29:47,685
All fair questions.

342
00:29:48,265 --> 00:29:56,227
So let me give you a broad overview of my accomplishments and what you can expect from me over the next two years in both style and substance.

343
00:29:57,167 --> 00:30:02,148
My agenda as your representative will be driven by you, the residents, and by public input.

344
00:30:02,808 --> 00:30:03,928
It will be a collaboration.

345
00:30:04,368 --> 00:30:07,029
My goal is to be both transparent and accessible.

346
00:30:07,690 --> 00:30:11,172
As your city councilor, I have never shrunk from the big contentious issues.

347
00:30:11,792 --> 00:30:14,873
I will continue to take them head on as I always have.

348
00:30:15,734 --> 00:30:17,755
My message to the neighbors is this.

349
00:30:17,775 --> 00:30:19,375
I am your voice.

350
00:30:19,856 --> 00:30:20,916
I will continue to hear you.

351
00:30:21,296 --> 00:30:23,537
You always have a friend in Michael Marks.

352
00:30:24,218 --> 00:30:26,699
I will yield to no one in my support of the neighborhoods.

353
00:30:27,479 --> 00:30:32,822
During the past 16 years as your city councilor, I have dedicated myself to doing the people's business.

354
00:30:33,577 --> 00:30:37,259
And to this end, I've worked tirelessly to be worthy of your trust.

355
00:30:38,140 --> 00:30:46,825
Over that time, I've become experienced in a broad and expansive range of issues, and I would like to think I learned what makes Method heart beat.

356
00:30:47,726 --> 00:30:55,430
The revitalization of Method Square is central to our success as a thriving community on a cusp of a new, innovative future.

357
00:30:56,151 --> 00:30:59,253
Economic opportunities abound, but we must reach out for them.

358
00:30:59,893 --> 00:31:02,155
Today, one of those opportunities exists in plain view.

359
00:31:03,034 --> 00:31:06,556
three city-owned parcels of land on the eastern edge of Meffitt Square.

360
00:31:07,297 --> 00:31:17,123
As your city councilor, I will encourage an invigorated Office of Community Development to take a more proactive role in attracting new investment and to charting the future of our community.

