00:35:51,898 --> 00:35:55,839
I've also worked hard and pushed for better maintenance of all our school and municipal buildings.

411
00:35:56,520 --> 00:36:06,964
As chair of the Public Safety Committee, I helped make people aware of the deplorable conditions of the old DPW facility and was a positive vote to create a new one.

412
00:36:07,825 --> 00:36:12,047
I've been vocal on the rundown conditions of the police department and the fire stations.

413
00:36:12,927 --> 00:36:14,808
This past year, although in the minority,

414
00:36:15,228 --> 00:36:20,392
I was extremely vocal in requesting that our fire headquarters be renovated at the same time as our police department.

415
00:36:21,113 --> 00:36:30,540
I am never afraid to voice my opinions, ask the appropriate questions, and demand answers for what I believe is in the best interests of Medford.

416
00:36:31,281 --> 00:36:44,872
Within the last few years on the Medford City Council, I have moved for, fought for, been vocal on, and supported charter review, filing suit against our Board of Appeals for approving 11 variances and allowing 500 unit development in our city,

417
00:36:45,293 --> 00:36:52,855
without the proper traffic study, without the required parking spots, and then some, all of which would have crippled that neighborhood.

418
00:36:53,995 --> 00:36:58,436
That helped set the tone in this city that our neighborhoods have to come first.

419
00:36:58,936 --> 00:37:05,117
Our residents have to have a say and be included in what goes on development-wise in every area.

420
00:37:05,897 --> 00:37:14,139
I have supported the Senior Citizen Work Program, the hiring of a recovery coach and substance coordinator to help combat the opiate crisis.

421
00:37:15,421 --> 00:37:22,985
I am continuously requesting higher maintenance budget for our infrastructure, streets, sidewalks, parks, and municipal and school buildings.

422
00:37:23,666 --> 00:37:27,368
These basic city services and maintenance should take precedence in our budget.

423
00:37:28,088 --> 00:37:30,890
I helped eliminate the odd even parking ban during the winter months.

424
00:37:31,490 --> 00:37:35,132
I moved for an 18-month demo delay to protect Meffitt's historic properties.

425
00:37:35,712 --> 00:37:37,433
I've supported reducing the speed limit.

426
00:37:37,994 --> 00:37:41,836
I've requested new radar guns and speed monitor signs to make our streets safer.

427
00:37:42,975 --> 00:37:56,258
Air traffic noise awareness is a goal of mine, was a goal of mine, and after I spoke about it numerous times on the council floor, two wonderful representatives were appointed and are leading the charge in trying to get resolved and keep Medford educated.

428
00:37:56,898 --> 00:38:01,039
I'm advocating for and working on an ordinance to stop level three gas leaks.

429
00:38:01,479 --> 00:38:05,120
I support an ordinance that holds universities accountable for students that live in Medford.

430
00:38:05,580 --> 00:38:09,041
I've requested and will continue to request we hire a grant writer.

431
00:38:09,061 --> 00:38:12,662
I will continue to fight for transparency in government

432
00:38:13,073 --> 00:38:14,694
because I still believe it is lacking.

433
00:38:15,495 --> 00:38:22,261
Finding out about a plan about a new police station from the press is wrong, and I will continue to fight for transparency.

434
00:38:22,801 --> 00:38:25,664
If reelected, I will continue to be vocal and work on these issues.

435
00:38:26,244 --> 00:38:32,730
I will continue to request funding to hire an outside company to help this Medford City Council update its zoning ordinances.

436
00:38:33,290 --> 00:38:39,015
I will continue to request citizen advisory working groups and task forces to guide the city in future development.

437
00:38:40,420 --> 00:38:44,162
If re-elected, I will continue to work hard to make a difference within the city of Medford.

438
00:38:44,802 --> 00:38:48,504
I will continue to do my homework so that each and every vote I make is the right vote.

439
00:38:48,924 --> 00:38:52,326
The vote that I believe will benefit the city of Medford and our citizens.

440
00:38:53,006 --> 00:38:58,449
I promise that I will continue to be a leader and not a follower.

441
00:38:59,030 --> 00:39:01,451
I will never be an automatic yes vote.

442
00:39:02,071 --> 00:39:03,512
I will be an independent voice.

443
00:39:04,130 --> 00:39:08,493
I thank you for the support you've given me so far, and I ask for your vote on November 7th.

444
00:39:08,774 --> 00:39:09,034
Thank you.

445
00:39:25,403 --> 00:39:31,130
Thank you to the Democratic Committee for giving us this opportunity to speak tonight.

446
00:39:31,971 --> 00:39:36,657
It's a pleasure to be here, and it's been a pleasure and an honor to serve you, the people of Medford.

447
00:39:38,019 --> 00:39:39,160
My name is Fred DelaRusso.

448
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:41,223
I'm a candidate for re-election to City Council.

449
00:39:41,683 --> 00:39:44,685
I've served on the council for nearly 12 years now, six terms.

450
00:39:44,705 --> 00:39:47,746
I'm in the end of my sixth term, up for reelection to a seventh.

451
00:39:48,366 --> 00:39:51,968
I am part of a family that's lived in this community for four years.

452
00:39:51,988 --> 00:39:55,490
I'm the fourth generation of my family to live in Medford.

453
00:39:55,790 --> 00:39:58,712
I'm the third generation of my family to live in the same house.

454
00:39:59,292 --> 00:40:04,675
I had to buy the house from my father, but it was the house that he had to buy from his father as well.

455
00:40:05,875 --> 00:40:08,417
And I'm the third generation of my family to operate a business in Medford.

456
00:40:09,838 --> 00:40:10,618
I love this city.

457
00:40:10,778 --> 00:40:16,182
I've had a lot of opportunity in my life to do other things, but this is where I choose to be.

458
00:40:16,623 --> 00:40:21,847
This is where I choose to serve, to live out my family's heritage of service in this community.

459
00:40:22,287 --> 00:40:25,029
It's something that's shaped who I am as a person.

460
00:40:25,970 --> 00:40:29,332
The only time I lived out of the city was the 12 years I was in religious life.

461
00:40:29,873 --> 00:40:35,497
And that experience too, both academically and spiritually, shaped who I am as a person as well.

462
00:40:36,818 --> 00:40:37,919
And finally,

463
00:40:38,597 --> 00:40:44,001
One of the things that shaped me is doing the work of being a city councilor and serving all of you.

464
00:40:44,521 --> 00:40:46,122
It's been a good experience.

465
00:40:46,623 --> 00:40:49,024
It's been challenging at times.

466
00:40:50,125 --> 00:40:52,046
It's been disappointing at times.

467
00:40:52,587 --> 00:41:02,213
But at the end of it all, I'm glad I'm doing it and I want to continue to do it for all of you and for all of us because in that we grow and prosper together.

468
00:41:03,534 --> 00:41:05,736
I've learned a lot over my years on the council.

469
00:41:06,176 --> 00:41:12,320
And one of the greatest issues or lessons I've learned is that we only get things done by working together.

470
00:41:12,700 --> 00:41:28,749
So I could rattle off to you a long list of things that I've accomplished in the 12 years that I've served on this council, and I've had a share in virtually all of them that have happened in this city, though there are some that I perhaps can't put my name to.

471
00:41:29,249 --> 00:41:35,113
However, I've learned that nothing gets done here unless we're working together.

472
00:41:35,673 --> 00:41:41,376
We work together by listening to the community, and I've done that throughout the years, and I continue to do that.

473
00:41:41,796 --> 00:41:45,218
My opinion has changed on issues because of that.

474
00:41:45,878 --> 00:41:52,541
I was a skeptic with the Green Line, and yet I've come along, and I see its benefit.

475
00:41:52,841 --> 00:42:03,806
I was concerned on how it will affect many of the neighbors, but I've worked hard and long on that with many of you, and I've come along on that, and I see its benefit.

476
00:42:05,427 --> 00:42:19,590
I've established good relationships in this community among the greater business community because I'm a businessman, but also because I'm a city councilor, and I see how people who live here, work here, and invest in this community really make it a great place.

477
00:42:20,190 --> 00:42:24,831
I've established great relationships with the people who work in this building.

478
00:42:25,311 --> 00:42:31,232
That's how we get things done, by having solid, good, working relationships with people.

479
00:42:31,669 --> 00:42:34,871
The people who work in this building are committed to you.

480
00:42:35,512 --> 00:42:37,093
They are committed to you.

481
00:42:37,513 --> 00:42:40,155
They don't come here because it's a great building to work in.

482
00:42:40,635 --> 00:42:41,776
The bathrooms are terrible.

483
00:42:42,176 --> 00:42:45,258
This ceiling was caving in until a couple weeks ago.

484
00:42:45,859 --> 00:42:48,520
And the roof was leaking until a couple months ago.

485
00:42:49,101 --> 00:42:49,621
It's fresh.

486
00:42:49,861 --> 00:42:50,482
It's redone.

487
00:42:50,602 --> 00:42:51,643
We still got a ways to go.

488
00:42:52,884 --> 00:42:54,465
But people are committed to you.

489
00:42:54,505 --> 00:42:56,287
The people in public safety are committed to you.

490
00:42:56,687 --> 00:43:10,119
I was not afraid to stand alone, to move forward on the bonding of money, to begin the process of the new police station, which has been a long-term goal of mine, which we'll finally see come through.

491
00:43:10,599 --> 00:43:18,807
I've been honored to work with a group of people, one committee that sort of fizzled out in its momentum, through no fault of anybody, I think.

492
00:43:19,530 --> 00:43:23,834
But, and then to work with the new Revive Committee that's working on Medford Square.

493
00:43:24,315 --> 00:43:27,898
This is gonna be the thing that we're on the cusp of moving on.

494
00:43:28,379 --> 00:43:29,780
We're closer than ever before.

495
00:43:29,800 --> 00:43:30,861
There's stuff underway.

496
00:43:31,182 --> 00:43:32,683
We're building a new park in the square.

497
00:43:32,983 --> 00:43:37,268
We have possibly a hotel that's going out right next door.

498
00:43:37,968 --> 00:43:39,470
And plans are being drawn for it.

499
00:43:39,790 --> 00:43:42,253
And it's gonna be part of a revitalization

500
00:43:43,302 --> 00:43:48,364
a renewed program for the revitalization of Medford Square.

501
00:43:48,704 --> 00:43:51,965
I'm excited to be a part of that and I want to continue to work on that.

502
00:43:52,966 --> 00:43:55,467
I've been an advocate for education and improving it.

503
00:43:55,507 --> 00:43:58,007
It comes from my background as a Benedictine monk.

504
00:43:58,848 --> 00:44:04,710
Who better to know the importance of having a new library in this community than someone that shared in that Benedictine tradition?

505
00:44:05,530 --> 00:44:06,811
I'm enthusiastic for that.

506
00:44:06,831 --> 00:44:07,972
20 seconds.

507
00:44:08,433 --> 00:44:08,953
Thank you, Henry.

508
00:44:09,413 --> 00:44:16,978
I'm enthused to be working towards improvements in all of our squares.

509
00:44:17,519 --> 00:44:21,041
I'm also looking forward to continue to work on the budget.

510
00:44:21,101 --> 00:44:27,366
You know, this year was in my 12 years on the City Council, this was the best budget that I had the opportunity to work on.

511
00:44:27,961 --> 00:44:35,889
and I'm gonna work hard to give you a new budget, and I ask for your vote, November 7th, for Del Russo number three, two, on the ballot.

512
00:44:36,970 --> 00:44:38,571
Thank you, Councilor Del Russo.

513
00:44:46,479 --> 00:44:47,080
Robert Cappucci.

514
00:44:59,579 --> 00:45:06,482
Thank you to the organizers for this event tonight, so that these candidates can come and bring our message to the city of Medford.

515
00:45:07,363 --> 00:45:08,223
I'm Robert Capucci.

516
00:45:08,363 --> 00:45:09,624
I'm 47 years old.

517
00:45:10,164 --> 00:45:12,345
I'm the youngest of seven kids in my family.

518
00:45:12,825 --> 00:45:14,646
I'm a lifelong Medford resident.

519
00:45:15,406 --> 00:45:18,768
I graduated from Franklin Pierce College in 1994.

520
00:45:18,828 --> 00:45:28,692
I went into teaching, and then after a few years of that, I joined the Army Reserves, and I currently work in electronics, making laser scalpels for a company up in Lexington.

521
00:45:29,743 --> 00:45:32,000
I heard a lot of the candidates touch upon

522
00:45:32,620 --> 00:45:42,706
The issues that were sent to us, the city committee here sent us actually 30 different topics to discuss with five minutes to talk.

523
00:45:42,746 --> 00:45:45,808
So I chose five, and I'm going to just answer them directly.

524
00:45:46,449 --> 00:45:49,531
The number one I chose was the opioid crisis.

525
00:45:50,471 --> 00:45:54,494
I lost my best friend in 2003 to drug addiction.

526
00:45:55,374 --> 00:46:01,218
A couple weeks ago, at 46 years old, he had to bury a high school graduate, a classmate of mine.

527
00:46:01,818 --> 00:46:08,383
It's the number one killer of people under 50 years old in America, and it needs to be addressed.

528
00:46:09,203 --> 00:46:22,732
I think Medford should start leading the way in research and how many prescriptions are actually being given for opioids, to whom, for what purposes, and to investigate to our fullest to ensure every single prescription is right and proper.

529
00:46:23,333 --> 00:46:25,254
I will continue to support and advocate

530
00:46:25,701 --> 00:46:41,168
for worthwhile community programs like candlelight vigils, various drug addiction rehab facilities and groups, and other initiatives we have here in Medford such as Team Medford and the new drug officer recently appointed by the mayor's office.

531
00:46:41,669 --> 00:46:46,271
I'd also like to establish here in Medford a kind of a tough love approach.

532
00:46:46,767 --> 00:47:09,295
and send out coordinated, communicated messages to all the residents on a regular basis to get people to realize their problem and light a fire under their butts to get the help that they need so they stop dying and they can enjoy the holidays, child graduations, weddings, all the things that make this life worth living.

533
00:47:09,675 --> 00:47:12,376
The Memphis City Council should start leading the way on this initiative.

534
00:47:13,937 --> 00:47:16,018
The next topic I want to talk about is inclusion.

535
00:47:17,079 --> 00:47:29,444
I think the best way we can be more inclusive of our diversity here in Medford is something that I've been calling for throughout my campaign and for years before.

536
00:47:31,362 --> 00:47:41,356
and it was highlighted just last night in these chambers by the excellent speech of Dr. John Stirella of Metcalf Street in two words, term limits.

537
00:47:41,877 --> 00:47:48,526
If we had a three-term term limit for the elected right now in Medford, there would be five open seats on this council.

538
00:47:48,846 --> 00:47:51,747
for this city to take advantage of and run for.

539
00:47:52,147 --> 00:47:53,928
There would be four seats on the school committee.

540
00:47:54,208 --> 00:47:57,049
We'd have two new challenging candidates for mayor.

541
00:47:58,349 --> 00:48:13,554
Nothing else would lead the way to include the diverse population we have in Medford so that we can hear from all different kinds of people to come up here and act, all different new ideas, new initiatives to include all of Medford in our wonderful city.

542
00:48:14,455 --> 00:48:14,875
Parking.

543
00:48:15,535 --> 00:48:18,596
I recently had a conversation with the manager of Carol's Restaurant.

544
00:48:20,013 --> 00:48:24,336
We discussed something that was recently featured on a news program, Chronicle.

545
00:48:24,876 --> 00:48:45,846
That report was called the Amazon effect, whereby mom-and-pop shops across Medford, across Massachusetts, across the country are getting walloped because more people can easily just go online and order from various, you know, internet services, and they're not being able to keep up with

546
00:48:46,423 --> 00:48:48,607
these internet companies, the mom and pop shops.

547
00:48:48,987 --> 00:48:54,698
So what cities and towns are doing to combat this and make our city squares more attractive is

548
00:48:55,864 --> 00:48:57,946
Offer no-fee parking.

549
00:48:58,446 --> 00:49:01,708
I lead the way to get us out of the contract with Republic Parking.

550
00:49:02,048 --> 00:49:03,990
We need to revitalize these city squares.

551
00:49:04,050 --> 00:49:05,150
That's the best way to do it.

552
00:49:05,471 --> 00:49:21,962
If we offer no-fee parking with strict two-hour limits so that we don't have that problem we used to have that's probably still going on on the outskirts of the city, we make sure that people that come here and park and leave their cars all day, after two hours, they're towed at their own expense.

553
00:49:24,123 --> 00:49:24,604
Taxes.

554
00:49:26,075 --> 00:49:31,819
I am actually for the city to collect more taxes and have more taxes in their coffers.

555
00:49:33,920 --> 00:49:40,904
We need these funds for hiring more police, firefighters, teachers, teachers' aides, infrastructure repairs.

556
00:49:41,425 --> 00:49:42,785
What I don't believe in... 20 seconds.

557
00:49:43,686 --> 00:49:44,006
Oh, really?

558
00:49:44,026 --> 00:49:44,847
That quick already?

559
00:49:45,007 --> 00:49:45,487
Gee whiz.

560
00:49:47,820 --> 00:49:51,142
Well, what I don't believe in is constantly raising the tax rate.

561
00:49:51,282 --> 00:49:56,245
What I think is what we do is we create more taxpayers, and the way we do that is to cut taxes.

562
00:49:56,605 --> 00:50:02,589
With my last few seconds, I want to make an appeal to the 28,000 registered voters who don't vote.

563
00:50:02,789 --> 00:50:05,731
Come out and vote on November 7th for Robert Cappucci.

564
00:50:05,771 --> 00:50:06,111
Thank you.

565
00:50:06,351 --> 00:50:06,831
That was really good.

566
00:50:08,432 --> 00:50:09,933
Thank you, Mr. Cappucci.

567
00:50:16,163 --> 00:50:22,568
Next two years, we'll give you 20 minutes, and we will charge you extra money.

568
00:50:24,329 --> 00:50:25,030
George Sacco.

569
00:50:34,057 --> 00:50:35,298
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen.

570
00:50:35,818 --> 00:50:36,459
Thank you for coming.

571
00:50:38,200 --> 00:50:41,343
My name is George Rick Sacco, and I'm a candidate for Memphis City Council.

572
00:50:43,284 --> 00:50:44,225
As a community advocate,

573
00:50:45,030 --> 00:50:47,472
volunteer, husband, father, grandfather.

574
00:50:48,593 --> 00:50:53,556
I want to work in bringing more leadership and positive action to the citizens of Medford.

575
00:50:54,897 --> 00:50:56,458
I'm a lifelong resident of Medford.

576
00:50:57,579 --> 00:50:59,841
I've been married for 46 years to my wife, Sandra.

577
00:51:00,281 --> 00:51:03,263
I have two sons, Brian and Eric, and six wonderful grandchildren.

578
00:51:05,165 --> 00:51:06,366
I'm a Medford High School graduate.

579
00:51:07,727 --> 00:51:10,849
I served three years in the United States Army, serving one year in Korea.

580
00:51:12,410 --> 00:51:14,772
I'm a veteran in pride

581
00:51:15,228 --> 00:51:16,868
in honor to have served my country.

582
00:51:18,889 --> 00:51:24,070
I attended Hampshire College, graduated with a business degree in management.

583
00:51:25,930 --> 00:51:32,011
I have retired from the General Electric Company after 38 years of service as a senior sales engineer.

584
00:51:34,471 --> 00:51:44,833
I was a member of the Mayor's Energy Commission for six years, and I received the Medford Green Award for citizen participation in that program.

585
00:51:46,818 --> 00:51:55,284
Medford has very specific needs that must be met to improve our quality of life in our neighborhoods.

586
00:51:56,865 --> 00:51:59,066
These are just a few of those needs that I've outlined.

587
00:52:00,387 --> 00:52:14,137
I can't get into specifics on each one, but I would like to discuss the opiate crisis, the charter review, and the street and sidewalk program, the issues which

588
00:52:15,213 --> 00:52:40,876
I should have mentioned, I am going to mention, uh, the charter review, sports zoning issues, adequate funding for our police and fire department, parking enforcement review of the existing contract, the opiate crisis and historical preservation of our buildings and our open spaces.

589
00:52:46,547 --> 00:52:48,308
I'd like to start with the opiate crisis.

590
00:52:50,490 --> 00:52:51,731
I want to give some statistics.

591
00:52:54,452 --> 00:52:57,234
Medford in 2015 was ranked 25 in opiate deaths in Massachusetts.

592
00:52:57,254 --> 00:53:00,056
2010 to 2015, 71 opiate drug-related deaths in Medford.

593
00:53:00,076 --> 00:53:02,518
2014, we lost 14 people.

594
00:53:02,538 --> 00:53:02,738
15, we lost 20.

595
00:53:16,613 --> 00:53:17,053
16, we lost 17.

596
00:53:17,093 --> 00:53:20,376
2017 numbers are in yet, but they're gonna be double digits.

597
00:53:20,396 --> 00:53:23,258
2016 to 2017, 610 deaths in Massachusetts alone, opiate and drug related deaths.

598
00:53:26,080 --> 00:53:27,341
July 2016 to June 2017, in this city,

599
00:53:44,741 --> 00:53:54,003
Our police department responded 52 times to narc drug users, basically brought back 52 people to life.

600
00:53:54,403 --> 00:53:55,223
We have a crisis.

601
00:53:58,664 --> 00:54:09,226
When I'm elected city councilor, I'm going to ask the administration for a line item in the budget geared specifically for the opioid crisis.

602
00:54:10,666 --> 00:54:14,387
And included in that budget, I'm going to ask the administration

603
00:54:15,326 --> 00:54:22,548
to supply and equip our police and fire first responders with the latest personal protection equipment.

604
00:54:24,048 --> 00:54:27,409
They're the first ones that go in these buildings, and the first ones as far as health issues.

605
00:54:28,669 --> 00:54:29,489
They have to be protected.

606
00:54:30,990 --> 00:54:35,611
As far as the charter review, 30 years.

607
00:54:35,631 --> 00:54:38,051
The charter is our most important document.

608
00:54:38,671 --> 00:54:39,792
It's like our Constitution.

609
00:54:40,852 --> 00:54:42,092
Our Constitution is looked at.

610
00:54:42,752 --> 00:54:43,533
Congress looks at it.

611
00:54:44,293 --> 00:54:45,073
The people look at it.

612
00:54:45,799 --> 00:54:47,400
We make changes, we don't make changes.

613
00:54:48,281 --> 00:54:49,762
We have to do that for Method.

614
00:54:49,782 --> 00:54:51,303
30 years, we have not looked at this charter.

615
00:54:52,544 --> 00:54:53,185
It's a review.

616
00:54:54,386 --> 00:54:55,287
The people vote.

617
00:54:55,787 --> 00:55:01,231
Whatever comes out of the commission, the people vote, any changes up or any changes down.

618
00:55:01,932 --> 00:55:06,475
So it is a people's involvement, the citizens of Method's involvement in the charter review.

