01:15:53,095 --> 01:15:59,419
The newly founded Library Foundation will play a vital role in raising private funds to help lessen the cost to the city of Medford.

814
01:16:00,379 --> 01:16:11,105
These projects are not taking place at the same time as many will lead you to believe, but with responsible fiscal policies, these all can be achieved within the next five to six years.

815
01:16:13,046 --> 01:16:19,770
Something that no one's talked about here at all is the issue of grave appointments, which is the status of the Lawrence Memorial Hospital.

816
01:16:20,880 --> 01:16:25,063
As our community grows in age, this asset of the local hospital grows in importance.

817
01:16:25,644 --> 01:16:30,447
Our seniors have become dependent on this facility for care for themselves and their loved ones.

818
01:16:31,047 --> 01:16:36,291
When you're having a heart attack or a stroke, that extra 10 to 15 minutes driving the ambulance can be vital.

819
01:16:36,812 --> 01:16:39,354
Or when you have a child that is injured or sick at 2 a.m.

820
01:16:39,374 --> 01:16:43,497
in the morning, the importance of having a medical facility minutes away is essential.

821
01:16:44,387 --> 01:16:53,012
I have been the only public official that has attended the Department of Public Health hearings and spoke out to keep this facility open and viable to our community.

822
01:16:53,032 --> 01:16:57,514
I'm telling you now, please don't let what happened in Baldwin happen here in Medford.

823
01:16:57,914 --> 01:16:59,715
An effective counselor is one who gets things done.

824
01:16:59,955 --> 01:17:04,498
Richard Caraviello was a counselor who doesn't talk about getting things done, but gets things done.

825
01:17:05,338 --> 01:17:13,763
Remember, government is about the people, and a core part of this principle is an attention to basic quality of life issues and responding to requests for basic city services.

826
01:17:14,506 --> 01:17:16,208
Your vote makes a difference and your opinion wins.

827
01:17:16,228 --> 01:17:16,808
Thank you.

828
01:17:16,828 --> 01:17:19,551
Again, I respectfully ask for one of your seven votes on November 7th, 2017.

829
01:17:20,571 --> 01:17:23,414
Ian, I am the number one name on the ballot.

830
01:17:23,474 --> 01:17:23,694
Thank you.

831
01:17:24,595 --> 01:17:27,958
Thank you, Counsel Caraviello.

832
01:17:33,823 --> 01:17:37,727
And last, but certainly not least, I haven't missed her name before, Cheryl Rodriguez.

833
01:17:49,231 --> 01:17:52,913
Hi, my name is Cheryl Rodriguez, and I'm running for a seat on the Medford City Council.

834
01:17:53,434 --> 01:17:56,156
Thanks to the Democratic Committee of Ward 6 for hosting us.

835
01:17:57,017 --> 01:18:03,842
When I received the email listing the nearly 30 City Council topics, my first reaction was, wow, that's a lot of stuff.

836
01:18:04,823 --> 01:18:07,705
I think that's what intrigued me about running for City Council.

837
01:18:08,005 --> 01:18:09,386
It's a pretty unique opportunity.

838
01:18:09,807 --> 01:18:13,449
You get to wear lots of hats, but it all boils down to quality of life.

839
01:18:14,270 --> 01:18:15,751
I'm a graduate of Medford High School.

840
01:18:15,852 --> 01:18:20,055
I have a daughter who graduated in 2014, and a nine-year-old in the Roberts.

841
01:18:20,656 --> 01:18:25,060
My parents also live in Medford, and my husband Alexis Rodriguez is a candidate for school committee.

842
01:18:25,721 --> 01:18:29,604
I'm a mom in the community who is heavily involved in the Roberts School PTO.

843
01:18:30,245 --> 01:18:37,932
I'm proud to say that I have committed to creating enrichment nights, running fundraisers, and applying for grants to help our children create memories at school.

844
01:18:38,790 --> 01:18:44,077
I'm grateful to the teachers and principal for trusting me and working tirelessly on these inclusive events.

845
01:18:44,838 --> 01:18:55,753
And thanks to all the parents who've helped in ways you never thought you would, like lugging a U-Haul's truck worth of yard sale items out of my house, or punching holes in nearly 600 pieces of artwork for our art show.

846
01:18:56,718 --> 01:19:01,241
I love Medford because there are so many great volunteer and service-oriented groups in the city.

847
01:19:01,921 --> 01:19:04,082
I would really like to find a way to link them all.

848
01:19:04,863 --> 01:19:08,985
Often I hear, I wish we had a group that was working on X, and oftentimes we do.

849
01:19:09,666 --> 01:19:16,170
I've met many amazing groups of people working to make the lives of people in our community better, and I've tried to help whenever I can.

850
01:19:17,030 --> 01:19:20,913
Many of the events that we enjoy throughout the city are run by volunteers.

851
01:19:22,908 --> 01:19:27,410
My commitment to the city made me want to run for city council to try to help in a different way.

852
01:19:28,011 --> 01:19:34,234
I've attended meetings, met with elected officials for years to try and get assistance on various issues and needs around the city.

853
01:19:34,774 --> 01:19:37,656
I've stood with Locust Street of Butters to stop overdevelopment.

854
01:19:38,176 --> 01:19:41,218
I've collected signatures outside Stop and Shop for charter review.

855
01:19:41,678 --> 01:19:50,523
I've advocated for airplane noise relief, fought for small class sizes, and to this day, I still continue to go to zoning board meetings and stand with residents.

856
01:19:52,777 --> 01:19:59,826
I want to be that person that you feel comfortable reaching out to, the one who will not only listen to your issue, but will dig in to find the best solution.

857
01:20:00,828 --> 01:20:05,914
I would also like to help push for a portion of our budget to be set aside for future maintenance projects.

858
01:20:06,577 --> 01:20:08,438
We all know that roofs don't last forever.

859
01:20:08,598 --> 01:20:11,320
It doesn't have to be a scramble every time one springs a leak.

860
01:20:11,900 --> 01:20:15,102
This will speed things up and help manage expectations.

861
01:20:15,582 --> 01:20:21,065
Money set aside each year in the budget for streets and roads will allow us to fix more in our limited construction season.

862
01:20:21,585 --> 01:20:23,747
This is just one part of our needed city plan.

863
01:20:24,407 --> 01:20:25,608
We hear that Medford is hot.

864
01:20:25,728 --> 01:20:29,250
We need to take control so that the projects being built here enhance our city.

865
01:20:29,910 --> 01:20:33,052
Medford needs to be a place where people work, eat, play, and live.

866
01:20:33,812 --> 01:20:39,356
A proper plan will keep us from turning into a bedroom community that creates no places for the people who live here to work.

867
01:20:40,237 --> 01:20:44,199
I see Mystic Ave as our blank space, our next big opportunity.

868
01:20:44,499 --> 01:20:49,103
I know a project with 500 apartments and a tiny amount of commercial is proposed for the center lot.

869
01:20:49,483 --> 01:20:51,204
I think placing it there would be a mistake.

870
01:20:51,624 --> 01:20:52,565
We need to think bigger.

871
01:20:53,125 --> 01:20:54,967
We need to stop the small-town thinking.

872
01:20:55,447 --> 01:20:58,569
Projects should not be approved because it is better than what is there now.

873
01:20:59,049 --> 01:21:00,871
Yes, most anything is better than nothing.

874
01:21:01,251 --> 01:21:02,452
But remember, Medford's hot.

875
01:21:02,992 --> 01:21:05,213
Cities that are hot don't just take what is offered.

876
01:21:05,753 --> 01:21:08,053
We ask for what we want and what we need.

877
01:21:08,453 --> 01:21:10,174
That is how you move the city forward.

878
01:21:10,494 --> 01:21:12,114
That's how Medford will come alive.

879
01:21:13,095 --> 01:21:15,435
Mystic Ave could be our premier commercial area.

880
01:21:15,475 --> 01:21:22,317
It could hold lab space, office space, an entertainment complex, a beer garden, a doggie daycare, restaurants, a hotel.

881
01:21:22,337 --> 01:21:23,257
The sky's the limit.

882
01:21:23,937 --> 01:21:30,439
If there seems to be a need for some residential, it can be placed at an extreme end of the street to not impact our commercial growth.

883
01:21:31,299 --> 01:21:41,972
Picture a center island with trees on it, bike lanes, beautiful wide sidewalks, a shuttle to the train station, another bringing people to the square to enjoy lunch, dinner, a show at the Chevalier Theater.

884
01:21:42,453 --> 01:21:47,099
This is the biggest opportunity in Medford to create this shining new district.

885
01:21:47,739 --> 01:21:48,981
All we have to do is ask for it.

886
01:21:49,421 --> 01:21:49,982
Don't settle.

887
01:21:50,843 --> 01:21:53,625
While we're at it, we should move to our zoning reform.

888
01:21:54,065 --> 01:22:14,717
In addition to stopping overdevelopment and parcelization that is burdening our neighborhoods, our zoning should be updated so that all new construction housing projects that don't meet the threshold to add affordable units pay into our housing affordability fund to be used in conjunction with CPA money to create affordable housing in Medford.

889
01:22:15,037 --> 01:22:19,320
This is a minor ask and one that other cities don't hesitate to require.

890
01:22:19,980 --> 01:22:23,662
Medford is growing, but like anything, we need to nurture it and guide it.

891
01:22:24,142 --> 01:22:29,145
In a well-planned city, that growth maintains a balance of commercial and residential.

892
01:22:29,506 --> 01:22:35,089
We need to leverage enough new commercial to be able to afford needed infrastructure improvements.

893
01:22:36,049 --> 01:22:38,911
I'm excited to dig in and be a part of this pivotal time in Medford.

894
01:22:38,971 --> 01:22:41,473
I'm a first-time candidate, long-time advocate for Medford.

895
01:22:41,513 --> 01:22:47,596
Please cast your vote for Cheryl Rodriguez, November 7th, and you have until 1159 tonight online to register to vote.

896
01:22:47,836 --> 01:22:48,417
Please do so.

897
01:22:48,517 --> 01:22:48,817
Thank you.

898
01:22:50,015 --> 01:22:52,557
Thank you, Mrs. Rodriguez.

899
01:22:57,860 --> 01:23:00,022
I don't think I'm the only one who observed it.

900
01:23:00,362 --> 01:23:04,085
All 14 candidates had done an excellent job tonight.

901
01:23:04,185 --> 01:23:06,366
I believe they are just... Let's give them a round of applause.

902
01:23:08,228 --> 01:23:08,648
Thank you.

903
01:23:09,589 --> 01:23:10,229
Job well done.

904
01:23:12,611 --> 01:23:18,815
So before we depart, my co-moderator Henry and I want to thank everyone who assisted us in putting this together.

905
01:23:19,216 --> 01:23:26,219
We especially want to thank Representative Paul Donato and Nancy White, co-chair of the Medford City Democratic Ward Committee, for their continued support.

906
01:23:26,619 --> 01:23:28,840
We thank our television crew member, Ralph Shouret.

907
01:23:29,220 --> 01:23:33,541
We thank the Medford Transcript, Medford Patch, and every other media that helped us advertise the event.

908
01:23:34,942 --> 01:23:38,203
Certainly, we need to thank the members of the Medford

909
01:23:39,405 --> 01:23:41,326
Democratic World Six Committee.

910
01:23:41,486 --> 01:23:42,667
They did an excellent job.

911
01:23:42,707 --> 01:23:44,909
Without them, we couldn't put this together.

912
01:23:45,449 --> 01:23:48,531
Can you stand up so you can be seen, member of World Six?

913
01:23:48,992 --> 01:23:49,812
Thank you.

914
01:23:49,832 --> 01:23:56,817
Stand up.

915
01:23:57,397 --> 01:24:00,139
With that said, I want to remind you, you heard it.

916
01:24:00,680 --> 01:24:05,103
What was recorded tonight will be rebroadcast in a few more days.

917
01:24:05,163 --> 01:24:06,364
I don't know when exactly.

918
01:24:06,904 --> 01:24:08,465
We shall find out by tomorrow.

919
01:24:09,057 --> 01:24:14,120
on channel 22 for Comcast or channel 43 and 47 for Verizon.

920
01:24:14,520 --> 01:24:22,305
I don't know the deadline because I know the prior event that we have are still, okay.

921
01:24:22,685 --> 01:24:27,468
I don't know if any of your friends failed to get in touch with City Hall today.

922
01:24:27,768 --> 01:24:34,532
I'm doing that as a citizen because I had friends who were supposed to call in today to register to vote.

923
01:24:34,552 --> 01:24:35,233
They couldn't do it

924
01:24:35,693 --> 01:24:37,876
because there was an issue with the telephone.

925
01:24:38,296 --> 01:24:41,721
I don't know how they deal it, so I don't know where we're standing on that.

926
01:24:41,801 --> 01:24:42,482
It's important.

927
01:24:42,822 --> 01:24:47,488
But most certainly, we must remember, vote on November 7th.

928
01:24:48,069 --> 01:24:49,351
Okay, thank you and good night.

